      {
        "id": "08e609e6-8850-4307-8070-a77a00186a8b",
        "score": 0.4750843,
        "text": "The document outlines the procedural steps for the NYISO, Aggregator, and Member System to conduct end-to-end testing of Aggregation telemetry communications:\n\n1. **Predefinition of Telemetry Object IDs**: The NYISO power system applications engineering group will define telemetry Object ID blocks for each Member System. These blocks will be used for Aggregations within the Member System's territory.\n\n2. **Enrollment of Aggregations**: When an Aggregator enrolls an Aggregation in the NYISO system, telemetry Object IDs from the Member System's predefined blocks will be assigned by NYISO DER enrollment staff. Each Aggregation will receive a unique set of telemetry Object IDs.\n\n   - A complete list of applicable Object IDs is available in the NYISO Direct Communications Procedure document, which requires a request through the NYISO\u2019s Stakeholder Services department.\n\n3. **Communication and Approval**: The NYISO Distributed Resources Operations (DRO) will email relevant parties, including the Aggregator and Member System, after obtaining approval for each Aggregation. The email will include:\n\n   - Contact information for the Aggregator\n   - Aggregation ID(s)\n   - Applicable Telemetry Object ID(s)\n   - Transmission Node PTID(s)\n   - Aggregation Type(s)\n\n4. **Configuration and Testing**: Member Systems must configure the Aggregations and test communication between the Aggregator control center and Member System control center. The Aggregator is responsible for scheduling this test with the Member System.\n\nContact information for the Member System is available through the provided link to the Distributed Energy Resources (DER) - NYISO.",
