      {
        "id": "f9f867be-4249-43ad-b3c9-e5780a0ee395",
        "score": 0.47062886,
        "text": "The document is an agreement for purchasing or selling unforced capacity in NYISO Installed Capacity Auctions, version 5.0. It outlines the terms under which market participants, referred to as \"Offerors\" or \"Bidders,\" engage in capacity auctions administered by the New York Independent System Operator (NYISO). \n\nKey points include:\n\n1. **Auction Types**: The NYISO conducts \"Strip\" auctions twice a year and \"Monthly\" auctions 12 times a year, where Offerors may sell and Bidders may purchase unforced capacity. Additionally, \"Spot Market\" auctions occur 12 times a year.\n\n2. **Market Participation**: Participants may act as either sellers or buyers in these auctions. The agreement governs bids to purchase and offers to sell unforced capacity.\n\n3. **Bid and Offer Packages**: Participants must submit properly formatted bids or offers, known as \"Electronic Bids\" or \"Electronic Offers,\" through the ICAP Automated Market System. These submissions are binding and will be analyzed according to the ISO Services Tariff and ICAP Manual.\n\n4. **Supersession of Prior Agreements**: Any previous agreements related to the purchase or sale of unforced capacity will remain effective until the implementation of the ICAP Automated Market System, after which this agreement will take precedence.\n\nThe document ensures that all market activities are conducted in accordance with the established rules and procedures of the NYISO.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/NYISO/protocol/Installed_Capacity_Manual_Attachments/page_11.jpg",
