        "id": "66fd90b6-22c6-4a42-86ed-49b5161ac73d",
        "score": 0.45969173,
        "text": "The document is a notification template from the New York Independent System Operator (NYISO) for generating facilities or aggregations entering the Installed Capacity (ICAP) Market. It is titled \"Attachment G Notification Template.\"\n\nKey elements include:\n\n- **Template Instructions**: Users are instructed to replace bracketed sections with specific data before execution.\n- **Address and Contact Information**: Spaces for the current date, customer name, and address are provided.\n- **Recipient**: The notification is addressed to the Manager of ICAP Market Operations at NYISO.\n- **Subject**: The subject line indicates the intent to qualify a new resource as an ICAP supplier.\n- **Content**: The main body states that the Market Participant (MP) intends to qualify a new generating resource as an Installed Capacity Supplier. It references compliance with Section 4.2.5 of the Installed Capacity Manual.\n- **Details Required**: \n  - Customer Name\n  - Resource Name\n  - Resource ID (NYISO-issued PTID or Aggregation ID)\n  - DMNC Rating\n  - Resource Location (City/State), with additional requirements if located in an External Control Area.\n\nThe template is part of the NYISO Capacity Market Products documentation.",
        "metadata": {
