        "id": "23cb7c5d-d73d-4beb-81db-57035acc083c",
        "score": 0.45632118,
        "text": "The document is from the New York ISO Transmission Congestion Contracts Manual. It outlines the requirements for submitting a Transmission Adequacy Data (TAD) request. The request must include:\n\n1. A description of the individual's role within the organization.\n2. A detailed description of the intended use of the requested information.\n\nThe NYISO will not process the TAD request until all steps are completed and documents reviewed. Access to the CEII Request Form and NDA is available in the \"Useful Links\" section of the Transmission Congestion Contracts page on the NYISO website.\n\nThe TAD includes power flow cases for the Auction and its contingency analysis, provided in Siemens\u2019 PSS\u00aeE raw data format, with contingency analysis data in a non-program-specific format.",
        "metadata": {
