      {
        "id": "ab37b080-593e-46d4-b625-711c3353282c",
        "score": 0.45541847,
        "text": "The document outlines procedures for Installed Capacity Offerors submitting offer packages to the New York ISO. \n\n### Key Points:\n\n#### 2.1. Submission of Offer Packages\n- Offerors must submit a complete Offer Package, including a Purchase/Sale Agreement and an Electronic Offer, during the specified Offering Period.\n- Purchase/Sale Agreements must be sent via overnight mail or delivery service, not via FAX or email, and will be time-stamped upon receipt.\n- Electronic Offers are submitted online and can include multiple Individual Offers. A new Electronic Offer overrides previous ones.\n\n#### 2.2. Invalidation of Offers\n- An Electronic Offer is invalid if submitted outside the Offering Period or missing required information.\n- An Individual Offer is invalid if:\n  - More than one location is specified.\n  - Resource name does not match the Offeror's holdings.\n  - Offer price is negative or not specified to two decimal places.\n  - Quantity of Unforced Capacity is incorrect or not specified to a tenth of a MW.\n  - Non-unique prices are given for the same Resource.\n\n#### 2.3. Multiple Offers from the Same Supplier\n- Details on handling multiple offers from the same supplier are not provided in the visible text.\n\nThis section ensures clarity and accuracy in the submission and validation of capacity offers.",
        "metadata": {
