        "text": "The document outlines requirements for Installed Capacity Suppliers seeking to import capacity into the New York Control Area (NYCA). It specifies the need for firm transmission documentation, which must include details such as supplier name, transaction reference number, service start and stop times, source and sink locations, service path name, and secured megawatts.\n\nFor suppliers importing from the Independent Electricity System Operator (IESO), written documentation of IESO's decision on capacity export requests is required. This documentation must be provided in advance of auctions to allow the New York Independent System Operator (NYISO) to review it.\n\nFor suppliers importing from ISO New England (ISO-NE), verifiable documentation is needed to confirm either an approved Export De-List bid in the ISO-NE Forward Capacity Market or that the supplier's resource is located in a specific ISO-NE Capacity Zone. This includes zones that are export-constrained or import-constrained and separate from the NYCA capacity zone.",
