        "text": "The document page outlines procedures related to the sale of Unforced Capacity in the New York ISO market. Key points include:\n\n1. **Dispute and Payment Obligations**: If a bidder disputes the Total Purchase Price, they must still pay as indicated. Overpayments or underpayments will be adjusted with interest, following FERC regulations.\n\n2. **Correction of Mistakes**: NYISO can revise Award Notices if mistakes are found, requiring bidders to pay or receive adjustments accordingly.\n\n3. **Sales of Unforced Capacity**:\n   - **Auction Conduct**: Auctions are conducted per ISO Services Tariff and ICAP Manual.\n   - **Electronic Offers**: Each offer is valid for one auction, and separate offers are needed for each auction.\n   - **Offer Details**: Offers must specify amounts, prices, and resources. The sale price is based on the Market Clearing Price unless from a Subject Generator, in which case ICAP Manual rules apply.\n   - **Binding Offers**: Submitting an offer package binds the offeror to sell the specified capacity.\n   - **Non-obligation**: Submitting an offer does not obligate NYISO to accept it, nor does it guarantee the sale of capacity.\n   - **Market Clearing Price**: This can be positive or zero.\n   - **Amendments**: Offers can be amended during the offering period, with all changes submitted according to the agreement and manuals.",
