        "text": "The document outlines terms related to the purchase and sale of Unforced Capacity by Market Participants in the New York ISO market. Key points include:\n\n1. **Qualification and Funds**: Market Participants must be qualified and have sufficient funds to purchase Unforced Capacity in an auction.\n\n2. **Transfer Conditions**: Unforced Capacity must be free of restrictions, taxes, and claims, except those specified in the ISO Services Tariff and ICAP Manual.\n\n3. **Capacity Limits**: The amount of Unforced Capacity offered cannot exceed the capacity allowed by the ICAP Manual for the Selected Resource.\n\n4. **Ownership and Authorization**: Market Participants must own or be authorized to purchase all shares of Unforced Capacity from the Selected Resource.\n\n5. **Market Commitment**: Unforced Capacity sold in an auction is committed to the New York Control Area and cannot be released until the commitment term expires.\n\n6. **Compliance**: Participants must comply with all legal requirements for holding and using Unforced Capacity.\n\n7. **Agreement Consistency**: The agreement must remain consistent with the original terms unless amended by NYISO.\n\n8. **Indemnification**: Market Participants must indemnify NYISO and its affiliates against any damages or liabilities arising from breaches of the agreement.\n\nThe document emphasizes compliance, legal obligations, and the protection of NYISO and its affiliates from liabilities.",
